sequenceDiagram
    participant User as External User
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Service as model-registry Service<br/>8443/TCP
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Container<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant REST as REST Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    Note over User,DB: Flow 1: External User Access (OAuth Mode)

    User->>Router: HTTPS Request<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Router->>Service: Forward to ClusterIP<br/>TLS Edge Termination
    Service->>OAuthProxy: HTTPS/8443<br/>Bearer Token
    OAuthProxy->>OAuthServer: Validate Token<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Service Account
    OAuthServer-->>OAuthProxy: Token Valid<br/>User Identity
    OAuthProxy->>REST: HTTP/8080 (localhost)<br/>No Auth
    REST->>DB: SQL Query<br/>PostgreSQL/MySQL Protocol<br/>TLS (optional)<br/>Username/Password
    DB-->>REST: Query Results
    REST-->>OAuthProxy: JSON Response
    OAuthProxy-->>Service: HTTPS Response
    Service-->>Router: Forward Response
    Router-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,DB: Flow 2: Internal Cluster Access (Non-OAuth Mode)

    participant Pod as Internal Pod
    participant ServiceHTTP as model-registry Service<br/>8080/TCP

    Pod->>ServiceHTTP: HTTP/8080<br/>No Auth
    ServiceHTTP->>REST: Forward to Container<br/>HTTP/8080
    REST->>DB: SQL Query<br/>Username/Password
    DB-->>REST: Query Results
    REST-->>ServiceHTTP: JSON Response
    ServiceHTTP-->>Pod: HTTP Response

    Note over User,DB: Flow 3: Operator Reconciliation

    participant Controller as controller-manager
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant WebhookSvc as webhook-service<br/>443/TCP

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch ModelRegistry CRs<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>WebhookSvc: Validate/Mutate CR<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>Webhook Client Certificate
    WebhookSvc-->>K8sAPI: Validation Result
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: CR Event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Resources<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,DB: Flow 4: Metrics Collection

    participant Prometheus as Prometheus
    participant MetricsSvc as controller-manager-metrics-service<br/>8443/TCP

    Prometheus->>MetricsSvc: GET /metrics<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS<br/>Bearer Token
    MetricsSvc-->>Prometheus: Prometheus Metrics
